{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"Included with: <b> πολύ-τροπος</b>, ον, <br /> (τρέπω) <b>much-turned,</b> i.e. <b>much-travelled, much-wandering,</b> epithet of Odysseus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.1, 10.330. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>turning many ways</b>: <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>shifty, versatile, wily,</b> of Hermes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Mercurium” 13, 439; τοῖς ἀσθενέσι καὶ π. θηρίοις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 291b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; and in this sense Plato took the word as applied to Odysseus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Hp.Mi.” 364e (_superlative_), +others\">Refs</a>]; τὸ π. τῆς γνώμης their <b>versatility</b> of mind, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.83 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ π., of Alcibiades, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Alcibiades” 24. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>fickle,</b> ὅμιλος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD(?): Pseudo-Phocylidea 95. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> of diseases, <b>changeful, complicated,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Numa” 22; also πόλεμος τοῖς πάθεσι ποικίλος καὶ ταῖς τύχαις πολυτροπώτατος [prev. author] “Mar.” 33; στρατεία 4th-5th c.AD: Eunapius Historicus “Fragmenta Historica - HGM” p.223D. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>various, manifold,</b> ξυμφοραί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.44 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπιθυμίαι, ἐθισμοὶ τῶν λέξεων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 471, “Nat.” 28.1 (p.7V.); κακά 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.567; ἔθνη 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Marcellus” 12; τύχαι [prev. author] Alcaeus2; ὄργια “Lyrica Alexandrina Adespota” 36.3; τὸ π. 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ σημείων καὶ σημειώσεων” 26 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> <b>-πως</b> <b>in many manners,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Meno Medicus “Iatrika” 20.31, 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.512, NT.Heb.1.1, 4th c.AD: Iamblichus Philosophus “de communi mathematica scientia” 12 \">NT+4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i>, -ωτέρως καὶ ποικιλωτέρως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “De rerum natura - Wien. Stud.” 5 G. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4187","accentedUnicode":"πολυτρόπως","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4183","matchingForm":"πολύς","stepTransliteration":"polus","gloss":"much","_zh_tw_Gloss":"許多","_es_Gloss":"mucho","_zh_Gloss":"许多"},{"strongNumber":"G5158","matchingForm":"τρόπος","stepTransliteration":"tropos","gloss":"way","_zh_tw_Gloss":"樣, 像, 方法","_es_Gloss":"manera","_zh_Gloss":"样, 像, 方法"}],"shortDef":"in various ways","mediumDef":"in various ways <br /><b>in many ways, in various modes,</b> <ref='Heb.1.1'>Heb. 1:1</ref>*","stepGloss":"in many ways","stepTransliteration":"polutropōs","count":1,"_es_Definition":"adv. en muchas formas","_zh_tw_Definition":"用許多種方式 (來 1:1)","_zh_Definition":"用许多种方式 (来 1:1)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"nhiều cách. πολύς (G4183) + τρόπος (G5158)","_zh_tw_Gloss":"多方","_es_Gloss":"de muchas maneras","_zh_Gloss":"多方"}]}